description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit friendly and conscientious Domestic Assistants to work at Hexham General Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Part time 15 hours per week, Monday to Friday 17:00 to 20:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Domestic services operate between 07:00 20:00.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Duties Include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning of floor areas as scheduled by means of vacuuming, mopping, spray cleaning and using cleaning machines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Removal of rubbish including domestic and clinical waste from designated areas to disposal point&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning of sanitary areas, toilet, sinks, shower cubicles and staff changing areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Damp dusting of all surfaces, ledges, shelves, curtain rails&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning of internal glass&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking down and putting up of curtains&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scheduled cleaning of chairs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scheduled cleaning of carpets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To wash walls (shoulder height) fitting and windows where required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other cleaning tasks as required. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Uniform will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note that NHFML is a wholly owned subsidiary of Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust. The successful applicant will be an employee of the subsidiary and not the NHS. Please note the terms and conditions are closely aligned to that of the NHS.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 11th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yvonne Holliday Domestic Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;yvonne.holliday@nhct.nhs.uk 0344 811 8111 or ext. 35072&lt;/p&gt;
